<author><name><![CDATA[Grapeshot]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-09-28T17:32:02-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-09-28T17:32:02-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10542&amp;p=118792#p118792</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10542&amp;p=118792#p118792"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NEStress wavy scanline effect doesn't work on my emu?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10542&amp;p=118792#p118792"><![CDATA[
NEStress is using a <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Sprite_0#Sprite_0" class="postlink">Sprite 0 Hit</a> to determine the screen position and when to stop changing the PPU scroll. it reads the register until a pixel of sprite 0 is drawn on top of a pixel in the background which will set a bit flag in a PPU register. You will need to have this working correctly to run all NES games except the very simplest. Super Mario Bros. won't even get past the title screen without it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4844">Grapeshot</a> — Sat Sep 28, 2013 5:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
