<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10542&amp;p=118750#p118750"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: NEStress wavy scanline effect doesn't work on my emu?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10542&amp;p=118750#p118750"><![CDATA[
The code should only be messing with fine scroll for part of the screen, so if your emulator extends it to the entire screen every frame, your emulator is apparently running too fast. Look closely; is the effect over the entire screen every frame, or does it affect part of each frame, the part moving around vertically so that it looks like it's affecting the entire frame? If this, then something is preventing the code from synchronizing to vertical blanking.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Fri Sep 27, 2013 10:48 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
